cdata.name: Miner One token
cdata.desc: Miner One is a different breed of mining operation. It cant be labelled a miningpool,because it doesnt rely on participants computing power. It cant be catalogued as the familiar and standart mining companies we are used to,as it doesnt rent hashing power and charge administrative fees. The main difference and what's at the basis of the Miner One business model is the ERC20 MIO Token, which represents membership in the Miner One community and a share of what the Miner One mines.
